{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782802015,"nonce":"NUV4v2nxzB4cEj8Mwo4OWmUUc1Q=","title":"Document MySQL backend differences \u0026 limitations (user-facing)","message":"Write a consolidated, user-facing 'MySQL backend: differences \u0026 limitations' reference (README section and/or squealy-mysql crate docs), drawn from the ca9891a audit. Today these facts are scattered across code comments and the README; a single authoritative list helps users pick/operate the MySQL backend.\n\n## Cover at least\n- **Type codecs**: uuid (CHAR(36) text), Json\u003cT\u003e (JSON via serde), time/chrono/SystemTime (TIMESTAMP, UTC, whole-second). Note the feature flags and the UTC-session requirement (Mysql::connect sets time_zone='+00:00'; MysqlConnection::new does not).\n- **Whole-second timestamp resolution** and the **TIMESTAMP 1970..2038 UTC range** (codecs reject outside it). Cross-reference ec9458d (sub-second precision).\n- **Compile-time-gated pg-only features**: RETURNING, FULL JOIN, date_trunc/AT TIME ZONE (Supports* marker traits) — code using them won't compile against MySQL.\n- **Cleanly-rejected DDL**: partial/filtered/expression indexes (io::Error at render). Already noted in README; consolidate.\n- **Intentionally unimplemented**: prepared statements.\n- **Dialect divergences that work but differ**: NULLS FIRST/LAST emulation, FOR SHARE -\u003e LOCK IN SHARE MODE, ILIKE -\u003e collation, CONCAT, integer division, EXTRACT(SECOND), UPDATE...FROM/DELETE...USING as JOIN, ON DUPLICATE KEY UPDATE.\n- **No expression canonicalization** (no canonical.rs equivalent) — partial-index/check diff fidelity; relates to 108fdfc.\n\nLow priority (docs only; no behavior change). Split from ca9891a, which closed the functional type-codec gap and recorded the audit in a bug comment.","files":null}]}